This paper is about dialogue systems and neural response generation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach that combines retrieval-based and generation-based methods, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the second likely sub-category. The paper also uses an encoder-decoder framework and adversarial training, which are common techniques in deep learning and machine learning, respectively, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the third likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval and ranking of response candidates, which are related to search engines and information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a discriminator to evaluate the quality of generated responses, which is related to neural networks and reinforcement learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) the fifth likely sub-category.
